cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.SE, cs.PL

The paper focuses on the security of Cyber-Physical Systems (CPS) and related Supervisory Control and Data Acquisition (SCADA) systems, which are typically used in industrial control systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), followed by cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses the simulation of CPS components, which could fall under cs.SE (Software Engineering) or cs.PL (Programming Languages).
